'''Yan Diomande''' (born 14 November 2006) is an Ivorian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[RB Leipzig]] and the [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Abidjan]], Diomande moved to the United States when he was 15 and joined [[DME Academy]] in 2022, after playing high school association football for the [[Yulee High School|Yulee Hornets]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dmeacademy.com/diomande-players-that-dominated/|title=DME’s Yan Diomande Named to ’23 Male Players That Dominated 2023′|publisher=DME Academy|date=27 December 2023|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref> At the side, he was named 2023 STARI Player of the Year<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dmeacademy.com/diomande-stari-poy/|title=Yan Diomande Named STARI Player of the Year|publisher=DME Academy|date=7 September 2023|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref> and also helped their affiliate team Frenzi to win the 2023 [[United Premier Soccer League]] Premier Division.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dmeacademy.com/diomande-as-frenzi-title/|title=ICYMI: Diomande Leads AS Frenzi to 2023 UPSL Title|publisher=DME Academy|date=16 August 2023|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref>

In October 2023, Diomande went on a trial at Scottish side [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibroxnews.com/2023/10/08/rangers-news-as-ivory-coast-sensation-yan-diomande-arrives-on-trial/|title=Rangers news as Ivory Coast sensation Yan Diomande arrives on trial|publisher=Ibrox News|date=8 October 2023|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref> but ended up not signing a contract and returned to DME.

===Leganés===
On 27 November 2024, Diomande agreed to a deal with Spanish [[La Liga]] side [[CD Leganés|Leganés]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdleganes.com/noticias/el-cd-leganes-incorpora-al-atacante-costamarfileno-yan-diomande-de-18-anos-de-edad|title=El C.D. Leganés incorpora al atacante costamarfileño Yan Diomande, de 18 años de edad|trans-title=C.D. Leganés sign the Ivorian forward Yan Diomande, aged 18|publisher=CD Leganés|language=es|date=27 November 2024|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://dmeacademy.com/yan-diomande-former-dme-star-makes-it-to-the-pros/|title=Yan Diomande Former DME Star Makes it To The Pro's|publisher=DME Academy|date=17 December 2024|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref> officially joining the club in January.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://premier.upsl.com/former-upsl-national-finals-mvp-yan-diomande-has-joined-la-liga-side-cd-leganes/|title=Former UPSL National Finals MVP Yan Diomande Has Joined La Liga side CD Leganes|publisher=[[United Premier Soccer League]]|date=15 January 2025|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref> Initially a member of [[CD Leganés B|the reserves]] in [[Tercera Federación]], he made his first team – and top tier – debut on 29 March, coming on as a late [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] for [[Juan Cruz (footballer, born 2000)|Juan Cruz]] in a 3–2 away loss to [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://as.com/futbol/primera/mbappe-salva-un-mal-dia-n/|title=Mbappé salva un mal día|trans-title=Mbappé saves a bad day|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=29 March 2025|accessdate=31 March 2025}}</ref>

Diomande scored his first professional goal on 11 May 2025, netting his side's second in a 3–2 home win over [[RCD Espanyol|Espanyol]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/705006/espanyol-leganes |title=Leganés 3–2 Espanyol |publisher=ESPN |date=11 May 2025 }}</ref>

===RB Leipzig===
On 16 July 2025, Diomande signed a five-year contract with [[Bundesliga]] side [[RB Leipzig]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rbleipzig.com/en/news/rb-leipzig-sign-laliga-prospect-yan-diomande-transfer-new-signing-2025-26-season|title=RB Leipzig sign highly rated winger Yan Diomande from LaLiga|publisher=RB Leipzig|date=16 July 2025|accessdate=16 July 2025}}</ref> after the club paid his [[Euro|€]]20 million release clause.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdleganes.com/en/news/yan-diomande-transferred-to-rb-leipzig|title=Yan Diomande transferred to RB Leipzig|publisher=CD Leganés|date=16 July 2025|accessdate=16 July 2025}}</ref> A month later, on 16 August, he netted his first goal for the club in a 4–2 away win over [[SV Sandhausen]] in the [[2025–26 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rbleipzig.com/de/news/liveticker-sv-sandhausen-rb-leipzig-dfb-pokal-1-runde-saison-2025-26-am-16-august-2025 |title=RBL erkämpft sich Pokalerfolg beim SV Sandhausen |publisher=RB Leipzig |language=de |date=16 August 2025 }}</ref> On 25 October, he scored his first Bundesliga goal in a 6–0 away win over [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://rbleipzig.com/en/news/review-bundesliga-fc-augsburg-vs-rb-leipzig-25th-october-2025 |title=An (almost) perfect day for RBL |publisher=RB Leipzig |date=26 October 2025 }}</ref> Later that year, on 6 December, he netted a hat-trick in a 6–0 win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]], becoming the second youngest player to achieve this feat in Bundesliga history behind only [[Walter Bechtold]] in 1965.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/rb-leipzig-eintracht-frankfurt-match-report-highlights-matchday-13-35095 |title=Yan Diomande hat-trick powers RB Leipzig to 6-0 victory over Eintracht Frankfurt |publisher=Bundesliga |date=6 December 2025 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/leipzig-dismantle-frankfurt-6-0-with-diomande-hat-trick-2025-12-06/ |title=Leipzig dismantle Frankfurt 6-0 with Diomande hat-trick |publisher=Reuters |date=6 December 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
On 27 May 2025, Diomande was called up to the [[Ivory Coast national under-23 football team|Ivory Coast U23]]s for a friendly.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mondialsport.ci/amical-u23-issa-fofana-abakar-sylla-malick-yalcouye-richard-kone-la-liste-des-elephanteaux-face-a-la-hollande-28847.sport|title=Amical U23: Issa Fofana, Abakar Sylla, Malick Yalcouyé, Richard Koné, … la liste des Eléphanteaux face à la Hollande|first=NAS|last=SARL|date=24 May 2025|website=Mondialsport.ci|language=fr}}</ref> He made his debut for the senior team later that year and was named in the squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fotmob.com/en-GB/topnews/24771-yan-diomande-could-be-breakout-star-afcon|title=Yan Diomande could be the breakout star of the AFCON|last=Roberts|first=Alex|date=24 December 2025|website=FotMob|access-date=11 April 2026}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/from-upsl-to-the-champions-league-yan-diomande-dominated-america-as-a-teenager-and-now-he-s-one-of-europe-s-hottest-prospects/blt1eefcc9417c33c71|title='I learned a lot' - How America shaped RB Leipzig star Yan Diomande, from UPSL to the UEFA Champions League|last=Hindle|first=Tom|date=14 January 2026|work=Goal.com|access-date=11 April 2026}}</ref>

On May 15, 2026, Diomandé was integrated by Ivory Coast coach [[Emerse Fae]] in his list of 26 players in order to compete in the [[2026 World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|access-date=2 June 2026 |date=15 May 2026 |language=fr |title=La liste de la Côte d'Ivoire pour la Coupe du Monde 2026 |url=https://www.fifa.com/fr/articles/liste-cote-d-ivoire-coupe-du-monde-2026 |website=[[FIFA]]}}<!-- auto-translated from French by Module:CS1 translator --></ref>

